{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MhgyoLn3EjwRyE3BSZWVHU","type":"tool_result","content":"Prometheus is running in the monitoring namespace.\nEnable Prometheus scraping for CockroachDB metrics from /_status/vars on port 8080.\nYou may use any Prometheus Operator-compatible approach.\n\nVerification:\n1. Prometheus has an active target for CockroachDB metrics.\n2. Metrics endpoint is reachable inside the cluster.=== PRECONDITION ===\n[precondition:crdb_env_ready:preconditionUnits[0] 'crdb_env_ready':probe] $ kubectl -n cockroachdb get pods 2>/dev/null | grep -c Running\n3\n\n[precondition:crdb_monitoring_stack:preconditionUnits[1] 'crdb_monitoring_stack':probe] $ kubectl -n cockroachdb get pod curl-test -o jsonpath='{.status.conditions[?(@.type==\"Ready\")].status}' 2>/dev/null | grep -q True\n\n[precondition:crdb_monitoring_stack:preconditionUnits[1] 'crdb_monitoring_stack':apply] $ /bin/sh -c 'kubectl create namespace monitoring --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -'\nnamespace/monitoring created\n\n[precondition:crdb_monitoring_stack:preconditionUnits[1] 'crdb_monitoring_stack':apply] $ kubectl apply -f cases/cockroachdb/monitoring-integration/resource/monitoring-crds.yaml\ncustomresourcedefinition.apiextensions.k8s.io/servicemonitors.monitoring.coreos.com created\ncustomresourcedefinition.apiextensions.k8s.io/podmonitors.monitoring.coreos.com created\ncustomresourcedefinition.apiextensions.k8s.io/prometheuses.monitoring.coreos.com created\ncustomresourcedefinition.apiextensions.k8s.io/prometheusrules.monitoring.coreos.com created\ncustomresourcedefinition.apiextensions.k8s.io/probes.monitoring.coreos.com created\n\n[precondition:crdb_monitoring_stack:preconditionUnits[1] 'crdb_monitoring_stack':apply] $ kubectl -n monitoring apply -f cases/cockroachdb/monitoring-integration/resource/prometheus-operator.yaml\nserviceaccount/prometheus-operator created\nclusterrole.rbac.authorization.k8s.io/prometheus-operator create